text: Damian Davey (born Damian Baker; 30 September 1964 â€“ 12 February 2017), better known as simply Damian, was an English pop musician. He was best known for his 1989 song "The Time Warp", a cover version of the original track from The Rocky Horror Show. He also did a cover of the song "Wig-Wam Bam" by the Sweet. He was born in Manchester. Damian died from cancer on 12 February 2017, at the age of 52. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:2017 deaths Category:Cancer deaths in England Category:English pop singers Category:Musicians from Manchester
